"⏎············className=\"fixed·z-[9999]\"⏎···········`",{"range":"7282","text":"7283"},"Replace `··········` with `··············`",{"range":"7284","text":"5985"},"react-hooks/refs","Error: Cannot access refs during render\n\nReact refs are values that are not needed for rendering. Refs should only be accessed outside of render, such as in event handlers or effects. Accessing a ref value (the `current` property) during render can cause your component not to update as expected (https://react.dev/reference/react/useRef).\n\n/tmp/workspace/mohitdebian/Kairo/src/renderer/src/components/Sidebar/SiteSettingsPopover.tsx:76:17\n  74 |       {isOpen && typeof document !== 'undefined' && ReactDOM.createPortal(\n  75 |         <div id=\"site-settings-popover\" className=\"fixed z-[9999]\" style={{\n> 76 |           top: (buttonRef.current?.getBoundingClientRect().bottom || 0) + 10,\n     |                 ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ Cannot access ref value during render\n  77 |           left: buttonRef.current?.getBoundingClientRect().left || 0\n  78 |         }}>\n  79 |           <motion.div ","Error: Cannot access refs during render\n\nReact refs are values that are not needed for rendering. Refs should only be accessed outside of render, such as in event handlers or effects. Accessing a ref value (the `current` property) during render can cause your component not to update as expected (https://react.dev/reference/react/useRef).\n\n/tmp/workspace/mohitdebian/Kairo/src/renderer/src/components/Sidebar/SiteSettingsPopover.tsx:76:17\n  74 |       {isOpen && typeof document !== 'undefined' && ReactDOM.createPortal(\n  75 |         <div id=\"site-settings-popover\" className=\"fixed z-[9999]\" style={{\n> 76 |           top: (buttonRef.current?.getBoundingClientRect().bottom || 0) + 10,\n     |                 ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ Cannot access ref value during render\n  77 |           left: buttonRef.current?.getBoundingClientRect().left || 0\n  78 |         }}>\n  79 |           <motion.div ","Error: Cannot access refs during render\n\nReact refs are values that are not needed for rendering. Refs should only be accessed outside of render, such as in event handlers or effects. Accessing a ref value (the `current` property) during render can cause your component not to update as expected (https://react.dev/reference/react/useRef).\n\n/tmp/workspace/mohitdebian/Kairo/src/renderer/src/components/Sidebar/SiteSettingsPopover.tsx:76:17\n  74 |       {isOpen && typeof document !== 'undefined' && ReactDOM.createPortal(\n  75 |         <div id=\"site-settings-popover\" className=\"fixed z-[9999]\" style={{\n> 76 |           top: (buttonRef.current?.getBoundingClientRect().bottom || 0) + 10,\n     |                 ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ Passing a ref to a function may read its value during render\n  77 |           left: buttonRef.current?.getBoundingClientRect().left || 0\n  78 |         }}>\n  79 |           <motion.div ","Error: Cannot access refs during render\n\nReact refs are values that are not needed for rendering. Refs should only be accessed outside of render, such as in event handlers or effects. Accessing a ref value (the `current` property) during render can cause your component not to update as expected (https://react.dev/reference/react/useRef).\n\n/tmp/workspace/mohitdebian/Kairo/src/renderer/src/components/Sidebar/SiteSettingsPopover.tsx:76:17\n  74 |       {isOpen && typeof document !== 'undefined' && ReactDOM.createPortal(\n  75 |         <div id=\"site-settings-popover\" className=\"fixed z-[9999]\" style={{\n> 76 |           top: (buttonRef.current?.getBoundingClientRect().bottom || 0) + 10,\n     |                 ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ Passing a ref to a function may read its value during render\n  77 |           left: buttonRef.current?.getBoundingClientRect().left || 0\n  78 |         }}>\n  79 |           <motion.div ","Insert `····`",{"range":"7285","text":"6052"},"Error: Cannot access refs during 